To progress from Year One to Year Two in an Integrated Masters programme, students must:
a) Achieve 120 credits at Level 4;
b) Pass at least 60 credits at the first attempt; 
c) Achieve a Year Mark of 50 at the first attempt.

Sources: [source_url: https://www.essex.ac.uk/-/media/documents/directories/academic-section/rules-of-assessment/pgt/2024-25/masters-taught-courses/five_year_integrated_masters_20-v7.pdf] (2024-25 academic year), [source_url: https://www.essex.ac.uk/-/media/documents/directories/academic-section/rules-of-assessment/pgt/2025-26/masters-taught-courses/five-year-integrated-masters-21-v7.pdf] (2025-26 academic year), [source_url: https://www.essex.ac.uk/-/media/documents/directories/academic-section/rules-of-assessment/ug/current/integrated-masters/roa-ug-integrated-masters-5yr-year-2.pdf] (2024-25 academic year)
